# YAMTAM ENGINE — Cursor Rules
# Source: core/rules/ (61 rules) · v0.17.0
# Full rule docs: https://phamlongh230-lgtm.github.io/yamtam-engine/

## Identity & Priority

You are an AI coding assistant operating under YAMTAM ENGINE governance.
Priority order (highest first): Security > Correctness > Consistency > Token optimization > UI quality.

This project uses: YAMTAM safety hooks + 8,550 skills + Rust runtime (yamtam-rt).
Read `AGENTS.md` first if you haven't. Then `gates/truth_gate.md`.

## Hard Prohibitions (never, under any circumstance)

- `rm -rf`, `rm -r`, `git push --force`, `git push -f`, `git reset --hard`
- `curl * | bash`, `wget * | bash`, `eval "$(curl ...)"` — remote code execution
- `DROP TABLE`, `DROP DATABASE`, `TRUNCATE TABLE`
- `chmod 777`, `chmod -R 777`
- Hardcoded secrets, API keys, tokens in any file
- Claiming PASS / DONE / CLEAN without running the actual command

## Code Constraints

| Metric | Hard limit |
|--------|-----------|
| Function length | 50 lines |
| Parameters | 5 (options object if > 3) |
| Nesting depth | 3 levels (early return to flatten) |
| File length | 300 lines |
| Cyclomatic complexity | ≤ 10 |

## Before git push — ALL must pass

```bash
bash core/tests/skills/test-skill-triggering.sh   # Result: PASS
bash core/scripts/verify-skills-lock.sh            # no drift
bash core/scripts/drift-check.sh                   # CLEAN
git status --short                                 # no surprises
```

## Verification law

Before saying "done", "fixed", "passes", "clean" — run the command, show output.
- "34/34 passed" ✅   |   "should pass" ❌
- "exit 0, 0 errors" ✅  |  "looks correct" ❌

## TypeScript

- No `any` — use `unknown` + narrow
- No `!` non-null assertion — use `?.` and `??`
- No `as Foo` without runtime verification
- Explicit return types on exported functions
- No `console.log` in production code

## UI / Frontend

- Colors: CSS variables or Tailwind semantic tokens — no raw hex
- Dark mode: required for every light mode token
- Contrast: ≥ 4.5:1 body text, ≥ 3:1 large text (WCAG AA)
- Font: system stack only — no loading external fonts without approval
- Type scale: xs=12px, sm=14px, base=16px, md=18px, lg=20px, xl=24px, 2xl=32px, 3xl=48px

## Scope discipline

- Declare which files you'll touch before starting
- Never write outside declared scope without asking
- Surgical changes only — don't improve adjacent code while fixing a bug

## Memory

- Architecture decisions → `core/scripts/add-fact.sh "tag" "fact" "high"`
- Never leave important decisions only in chat

## Skill format (if adding skills)

- YAML frontmatter: name, description, origin, license, version, compatibility
- Sections: When to Use, Do NOT use for, code examples, Anti-Fake-Pass
- Max 220 lines · Register in `core/config/skills-lock.json`
